i could apologize a thousand times. but i dont think it would get me anywhere this time. youve made it quite clear im not needed now. and please dont lie to me. because even though i will know you are, well ill make up excuses for you. ive coaxed myself into believeing you one too many times.

and youve read what i had to say. you were amazed but that was just a small bit of how i feel. if you only knew. that was over 14 days ago. and things have grew even more.

before i knew.

i think im in this a little more then you. well im looking up and i cant even see the ground, but i know you are up there just staring down at me. so what do i do? its not like i can climb back up now. so for some reason i thought maybe you could meet me down here. maybe you could save my life. either that or leave me to die in this hole ive dug myself one too many times. ill bury myself alive.

 

i could make you so much more happy. i would do whatever it takes. and im sorry if im not as good as her. i probably wont ever be. im sorry. i love you so much.

And as she looks off the side of the ship she thinks to herself, we're heading in the same place. Theres nothing but nothing; nothing but a vast openess ahead.  She feels bad for wasting this life, someone else could have done something so much more with this time. She feels tears regretfully letting her know shes still here. One more look ahead, this deep ocean goes on forever; forever holding nothing. This is her life.

Wow yeah so today was fun.  We didn't do much but yeah it doesnt take much for me and Britt to have fun.  Ohh yeah after school we decided to walk into the middle school to see if the note we had left on a board was still there and I saw this kid.  he was black.  okay and so yeah he had this watch on and it was on of those spinners. and so yeah i was curious and i went up to him and started spinning it.  what a cheap piece of shit.  but yeah i asked him if he got it out of the 50 cent machine cuz it sounded like plastic but he said no its real.  i made fun of him for about 56 hours after that.  i guess you had to be there cuz it was really funny.  then we saw ej.  then we went back to my house.  but yesterday when were walking back to my house we found this soccer net like one of the big real ones. and we decided to climb it.  it was so crazy we got to like the top but then we got stuck in the net so we were like hanging by our feet.  well sort of.  anyways so yeah today at around 4 Wassim picked me and Britt up and then he went to cash his check so he could buy me and Britt food.  So yeah then we went and picked Craig up and I dont know we just drove around.  NOOO omg it was so funny. Wassim was ordering our food and I dont know nevermind. I cant explain it but me and Britt seriously were almost pissing our pants.  And at the bank too.  But yeah and then that supposely "haunted" house off of Van Vleet.  We went there.  And Wassim was really scared.  So me and Craig wanted to go inside and so Britt decided to go too.  Well we walked up to the shed or something and we saw a rope hanging like what people hang themselves with..whats that called? yeah so Britt went back to the car and me and Craig and walked around and went inside and yeah it was odd, but gay.  There isnt even an actuall house.  

Okay so yeah back at my house.  Once again we almost pissed our pants.  We were throwing magazines at my fan.  And I swear to god it was by far the funniest thing I have ever seen.  We were doing it for about 15 minutes and in those 15 minutes it ended up destroying my room.  The magazines knocked over my speakers and clock and pictures and other things.  Yeah there were alot of other funny things but I dont remeber.

Oh yeah, I officially broke my phone.  It like well I was talking to Ryan on the phone and it like shut itself off and then turned back on again.  And he called me back and the ring got like all jacked up.  It was funny.  But not anymore because it wont turn on.  I dont know what Im gonna do cuz I might be screwed out of a phone until Christmas time.

Anyways. I LOVE RYAN BAKER.
